                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1927—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. Department finds in a note from the Cuban Embassy reference to a
                    communication of November 17, 1926 which Ambassador Crowder addressed to the
                    Cuban Government concerning reciprocity treaty. Send text at once in open mail
                    for Department’s files.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
